WorkingWiki is an extension to the MediaWiki platform that provides a wiki environment in which research teams can collaboratively write and maintain
* data files
* data processing software
* figures and other outputs
* and manuscripts for publication,
creating a powerful platform for open science.

WorkingWiki provides 
* revision control
* archiving 
* and publication 
of projects made up of source files and output targets, and lets editors 
* run and debug their code on-wiki.  
Advanced features include full support for LaTeX documents, job control for computing clusters, and Git integration.

